Description: The SE Standard 22 relives the days of old when Paul Reed Smith offered the all-mahogany body Standard model in 1985. The comfortable neck will feel right in your hands and the warm tone will catch every ear in the room. The SE Standard 22 is a workhorse guitar that is ideal for the studio and the stage. With an all-mahogany body and 22-fret set mahogany neck, this guitar has a warm, woody tone and focused midrange, allowing the SE Standard 22 to easily fit in a mix. This guitar is complete with classic PRS appointment, including an all-mahogany body (reminiscent of Paul’s pre-factory guitars), a set mahogany Wide Fat neck, rosewood fretboard and bird inlays, and humbucking pickups with a PRS-Designed stoptail. Since 2001, the SE Series has been offering incredible quality and great tone at affordable prices. The goal of the SE Series has always been to provide a quality instrument to players of all levels – one that would not fight the player, but encourage him or her to start and to keep playing.
Title: Paul Reed Smith SE Standard 22
ConditionDescription: Excellent condition, no scratches or visible blemishes, chrome hardware, smooth low action, pickups sound excellent, no disappointments here. Comes with gig bag, tremolo bar and ppwk is in gig bag.
